BASD urges Asia to help the euro area
The Asian Development Bank has asked India and China to prepare to help the eurozone emerge from the sovereign debt crisis to avoid a long-term decline that would hinder the development of the Asian economy.
Rajat Nag, the managing director of Manila-based BASD, said the two fastest growing economies in the world should "do everything in their power" to accelerate the recovery of the currency area through the International Monetary Fund or direct bilateral agreements.
