"Asia may be protected to a certain extent but it is not immune".
"So if China and India can help, let nothing stop them".
In recent months, the euro area has been seriously shaken by a sovereign debt crisis.
Recently, the cost of Italian debt has risen dangerously and the Prime Ministers of Italy and Greece have resigned.
The burgeoning sovereign debt crisis in Europe has raised fears that the global economy is about to enter recession, and has prompted calls from major emerging economies to come together to help the eurozone find a solution.
Mr Nag predicted that the IMF would channel any Asian aid, but he also said that this bilateral assistance - such as buying bonds from the US financial rescue fund, the European Financial Stability Fund - was offering greater bargaining power to Europe's Asian partners.
Anand Sharma, India's Minister of Commerce and Industry, said that "India will do everything it can" to help the eurozone as its own economy is now suffering from a drop in exports and a drying up of foreign capital inflows.
