The remains of the Saltillo-born pilot Bacio Cortés arrived (incinerated) at 18:05 to be handed over by the funeral home to the members of the Mexican Air Force, led by Major Jaime Martinez, on the esplanade of the group, where he was awaited by his family, including his daughter Amanda and his wife Cristina, his mother, his brothers and other relatives, students and teachers.
